// pond/agent/conversation — public shape types.
//
// Pattern 5 in the six-pattern catalog: pure data, no flow.
// Constructed via struct literal at use sites, returnable from
// fns by value through the m49 calling convention.
//
// Surface contract: pond/CONTRACTS.md § pond/agent/conversation/.

// Message — a single chat-history entry. `role` is one of
// "user" / "assistant" / "system" (we don't enum-constrain at v1
// because `role` is an opaque string the LLM vendors validate
// downstream). `content` is the message body verbatim.
// `ts` records when the message was appended; mirrors the
// `ts: Time` shape from `downstream-consumer::Tick` / `downstream-consumer::Quote`
// per the cross-cutting precedent.
//
// **Note on tab-encoding** (see `history()` in
// `conversation.hl`): role and content are appended into a
// single tab-separated stream when callers ask for the
// canonical "history()" representation. Embedded tabs in
// `content` would corrupt the stream; the conservative v1 stance
// is "callers don't pass tabs in content" — same convention
// `pond/router::RouteParams` and `pond/agent/llm::LlmRequest`
// already use. A future `std::iter::TabFields` (logged in
// FRICTION.md as duplicate-suspected) would centralize the
// pattern and could escape the delimiter properly.
type Message {
    role:    String = "";
    content: String = "";
    ts:      Time   = `1970-01-01T00:00:00Z`;
}
